This paper is about improving open information extraction (IE) through confidence modeling and iterative learning. The task of open IE involves extracting open-domain assertions from natural language sentences, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a binary classification loss to calibrate the likelihood of extractions, which involves machine learning techniques such as ranking and classification. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques such as precision and recall, which may place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the iterative learning process mentioned in the paper involves trial and error, which may suggest that the paper belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
